                            </figure>
                            
							<p>&nbsp;</p>
								<p>On 11th March 2018, though being a Sunday, 
								the Raghabpur campus came alive with almost 250 
								students celebrating Women's Day. Organised by 
								the social work &amp; NSS department along with 
								XADAM, over 100 girls from the main campus 
								joined together with 100 girls from the 
								Raghabpur campus to give meaning to the theme of 
								the day <b><i>'W for W' (Women for Women)</i></b>.<br>
								<br>
								Rev. Dr. Dominic Savio, SJ, Principal of the 
								College was overwhelmed to see this big 
								gathering. In his inaugural address, he 
								enlightened everyone present on how &quot;<b><i>Our 
								first identity is that of a human being</i></b>&quot;. 
								He continued to say, &quot;<b><i>We must respect 
								ourselves first and look at others from their 
								own eyes which is the best way to understand 
								them</i></b>.&quot;
								<a href="news/sxc-CollegeNews.htm#WomensDay-11Mar2018">
								Read more...</a> </p>
