							<p>&nbsp;</p>
								<p>
								The Annual Sports was held on 3rd February 2018 
								on the College Field and it was a pleasure to 
								welcome Mr. Arun Lal as our Chief Guest. The 
								Parade began with the BSF band setting the tone 
								and beat for all the Departments who had turned 
								out in their very best. Colourful costumes 
								depicting various themes were on display. The 
								College Flag was brought up by the Sports 
								Secretaries Arjun Ghose and Vrinda Todi along 
								with the General Secretary of the Students 
								Council, Akashnil Dutta Mukherjee and Assistant 
								General Secretary Navya Kothari. Our Principal 
								Rev. Fr. Dominic Savio welcomed the Chief Guest 
								and Vice Principal Prof. Bertram Da' Silva 
								felicitated Mr. Arun Lal with a memento. A very 
								inspiring speech was delivered by Mr. Arun Lal 
								who was greatly impressed by the Parade and the 
								enthusiasm of the students. This was followed by 
								a traditional Folk Dance put up by XADAM after 
								which the events began in right ernest. 
								</p>

								<p>
								Exciting events for Staff and Students were 
								conducted. The Championship events for Men and 
								Women saw close competition and the trophies 
								were lifted eventually by Janishar Akhtar (B.Sc. 
								2nd Year) and Krithi Rebello (B.A. 2nd Year). 
								After a gap of many years the Students team 
								defeated the Staff 2-1 in the Tug of War. The 
								relay races for Men, Women and Staff towards the 
								end of the Sports had the full crowd cheering 
								for their teams.
								
								
								<a href="news/sxc-CollegeNews.htm#AnnualSports2018">Read 
								more...</a></p> 
								

															
							
